# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SPECIFICATION OVERVIEW
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Purpose

The AI Regulations Compliance specification defines:
- **Regulatory Mapping**: Alignment with global AI governance frameworks
- **Risk Classification**: AI system risk categorization
- **Compliance Controls**: Required controls and documentation
- **Audit Requirements**: Evidence and traceability needs

## Key Regulatory Frameworks

| Framework | Jurisdiction | Focus |
|-----------|--------------|-------|
| EU AI Act | European Union | Risk-based AI regulation |
| Singapore MGF | Singapore | Model governance framework |
| NIST AI RMF | United States | AI risk management |
| ISO/IEC 42001 | International | AI management systems |

## Key Documents

| Document | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `regulations-spec.tex` | Main specification document |
| `chapters/03-regulatory-mapping.tex` | Framework alignment tables |
| `chapters/05-risk-classification.tex` | Risk tier definitions |
| `references.bib` | Bibliography and citations |

