# REQUIREMENT ID CONVENTIONS
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

| Category | Prefix | Example |
|----------|--------|---------|
| EU AI Act | REG-EU | REG-EU-001 |
| Singapore MGF | REG-SG | REG-SG-001 |
| NIST RMF | REG-NIST | REG-NIST-001 |
| Cross-cutting | REG-CC | REG-CC-001 |
| Audit | REG-AUD | REG-AUD-001 |

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# RISK TIER DEFINITIONS (Authoritative)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

These risk tiers are authoritative - all systems MUST classify according to these:

| Tier | Description | Examples | Controls Required |
|------|-------------|----------|-------------------|
| Prohibited | Unacceptable risk | Social scoring, manipulation | Not permitted |
| High-Risk | Significant impact | HR decisions, credit scoring | Full compliance |
| Limited | Moderate transparency | Chatbots, content generation | Disclosure required |
| Minimal | Low risk | Spam filters, recommendations | Basic documentation |

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CITATION FORMAT
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

When citing regulatory requirements:

```latex
\begin{tcolorbox}[colback=blue!5,colframe=blue!70,title=Regulatory Requirement]
\textbf{Source:} EU AI Act, Article 52(1) \\
\textbf{Text:} ``\textit{Providers shall ensure that AI systems intended to interact 
with natural persons are designed and developed in such a way that natural persons 
are informed that they are interacting with an AI system...}'' \\
\textbf{Applicability:} All customer-facing AI systems
\end{tcolorbox}
```

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DRIFT DETECTION COMMANDS
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

```bash
# Full audit for regulations domain
make audit-spec-drift-domain DOMAIN=regulations

# Check schema validity
python3 docs/schema/validate.py --domain regulations

# Verify source document currency
ls -la docs/regulations/
```

